      <h2>The True Cost of No-Shows</h2>
      <p>Every no-show doesn't just lose the appointment revenue — it wastes the artist's time, blocks a slot that could have gone to a paying client, and disrupts the entire day's schedule. For a studio with 5 artists averaging $150 per session, a single no-show costs $750 in lost billable time. Industry data shows most studios lose between 10-30% of booked appointments to no-shows — that's <strong>$12,000-$50,000 per year</strong> in lost revenue for an average shop.</p>
      <p>The good news? Studios that implement a deposit-first booking system consistently cut no-shows to under 5%. Here's exactly how to do it.</p>

      <!-- 内嵌数据图：No-Show Cost Calculator -->
      <div class="my-8 rounded-xl border border-ink-800 bg-ink-900/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-white mb-4">📊 No-Show Cost Calculator: What Each No-Show Really Costs</p>
